1139  //============================================================================
1140  // Method Description:
1153  template<typename dtype>
1154  NdArray<dtype> append(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, const NdArray<dtype>& inAppendValues, Axis inAxis)
1155  {
1156  switch (inAxis)
1157  {
1158  case Axis::NONE:
1159  {
1160  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, inArray.size() + inAppendValues.size());
1161  std::copy(inArray.cbegin(), inArray.cend(), returnArray.begin());
1162  std::copy(inAppendValues.cbegin(), inAppendValues.cend(), returnArray.begin() + inArray.size());
1163 
1164  return std::move(returnArray);
1165  }
1166  case Axis::ROW:
1167  {
1168  Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
1169  Shape appendShape = inAppendValues.shape();
1170  if (inShape.cols != appendShape.cols)
1171  {
1172  std::string errStr = "ERROR: append: all the input array dimensions except for the concatenation axis must match exactly";
1173  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1174  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1175  }
1176 
1177  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(inShape.rows + appendShape.rows, inShape.cols);
1178  std::copy(inArray.cbegin(), inArray.cend(), returnArray.begin());
1179  std::copy(inAppendValues.cbegin(), inAppendValues.cend(), returnArray.begin() + inArray.size());
1180 
1181  return std::move(returnArray);
1182  }
1183  case Axis::COL:
1184  {
1185  Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
1186  Shape appendShape = inAppendValues.shape();
1187  if (inShape.rows != appendShape.rows)
1188  {
1189  std::string errStr = "ERROR: append: all the input array dimensions except for the concatenation axis must match exactly";
1190  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1191  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1192  }
1193 
1194  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(inShape.rows, inShape.cols + appendShape.cols);
1195  for (uint32 row = 0; row < returnArray.shape().rows; ++row)
1196  {
1197  std::copy(inArray.cbegin(row), inArray.cend(row), returnArray.begin(row));
1198  std::copy(inAppendValues.cbegin(row), inAppendValues.cend(row), returnArray.begin(row) + inShape.cols);
1199  }
1200 
1201  return std::move(returnArray);
1202  }
1203  default:
1204  {
1205  // this isn't actually possible, just putting this here to get rid
1206  // of the compiler warning.
1207  return std::move(NdArray<dtype>(0));
1208  }
1209  }
1210  }

1212  //============================================================================
1213  // Method Description:
1232  template<typename dtype>
1233  NdArray<dtype> arange(dtype inStart, dtype inStop, dtype inStep)
1234  {
1235  if (inStep > 0 && inStop < inStart)
1236  {
1237  std::string errStr = "ERROR: arange: stop value must be larger than the start value for positive step.";
1238  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1239  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1240  }
1241 
1242  if (inStep < 0 && inStop > inStart)
1243  {
1244  std::string errStr = "ERROR: arange: start value must be larger than the stop value for negative step.";
1245  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1246  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1247  }
1248 
1249  std::vector<dtype> values;
1250 
1251  dtype theValue = inStart;
1252 
1253  if (inStep > 0)
1254  {
1255  while (theValue < inStop)
1256  {
1257  values.push_back(theValue);
1258  theValue += static_cast<dtype>(inStep);
1259  }
1260  }
1261  else
1262  {
1263  while (theValue > inStop)
1264  {
1265  values.push_back(theValue);
1266  theValue += static_cast<dtype>(inStep);
1267  }
1268  }
1269 
1270  return std::move(NdArray<dtype>(values));
1271  }
1272

1292  template<typename dtype>

1295  if (inStop <= 0)
1296  {
1297  std::string errStr = "ERROR: arange: stop value must ge greater than 0.";
1298  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1299  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1300  }
1301 
1302  return std::move(arange<dtype>(0, inStop, 1));
1303  }

1825  // Method Description:
1836  template<typename dtype>
1837  NdArray<double> average(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, const NdArray<dtype>& inWeights, Axis inAxis)
1838  {
1839  switch (inAxis)
1840  {
1841  case Axis::NONE:
1842  {
1843  if (inWeights.shape() != inArray.shape())
1844  {
1845  std::string errStr = "ERROR: average: input array and weight values are not consistant.";
1846  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1847  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1848  }
1849 
1850  NdArray<double> weightedArray(inArray.shape());
1851  std::transform(inArray.cbegin(), inArray.cend(), inWeights.cbegin(), weightedArray.begin(), std::multiplies<double>());
1852 
1853  double sum = static_cast<double>(std::accumulate(weightedArray.begin(), weightedArray.end(), 0.0));
1854  NdArray<double> returnArray = { sum /= inWeights.template sum<double>().item() };
1855 
1856  return std::move(returnArray);
1857  }
1858  case Axis::COL:
1859  {
1860  Shape arrayShape = inArray.shape();
1861  if (inWeights.size() != arrayShape.cols)
1862  {
1863  std::string errStr = "ERROR: average: input array and weights value are not consistant.";
1864  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1865  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1866  }
1867 
1868  double weightSum = inWeights.template sum<double>().item();
1869  NdArray<double> returnArray(1, arrayShape.rows);
1870  for (uint32 row = 0; row < arrayShape.rows; ++row)
1871  {
1872  NdArray<double> weightedArray(1, arrayShape.cols);
1873  std::transform(inArray.cbegin(row), inArray.cend(row), inWeights.cbegin(), weightedArray.begin(), std::multiplies<double>());
1874 
1875  double sum = static_cast<double>(std::accumulate(weightedArray.begin(), weightedArray.end(), 0.0));
1876  returnArray(0, row) = sum / weightSum;
1877  }
1878 
1879  return std::move(returnArray);
1880  }
1881  case Axis::ROW:
1882  {
1883  if (inWeights.size() != inArray.shape().rows)
1884  {
1885  std::string errStr = "ERROR: average: input array and weight values are not consistant.";
1886  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1887  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1888  }
1889 
1890  NdArray<dtype> transposedArray = inArray.transpose();
1891 
1892  Shape transShape = transposedArray.shape();
1893  double weightSum = inWeights.template sum<double>().item();
1894  NdArray<double> returnArray(1, transShape.rows);
1895  for (uint32 row = 0; row < transShape.rows; ++row)
1896  {
1897  NdArray<double> weightedArray(1, transShape.cols);
1898  std::transform(transposedArray.cbegin(row), transposedArray.cend(row), inWeights.cbegin(), weightedArray.begin(), std::multiplies<double>());
1899 
1900  double sum = static_cast<double>(std::accumulate(weightedArray.begin(), weightedArray.end(), 0.0));
1901  returnArray(0, row) = sum / weightSum;
1902  }
1903 
1904  return std::move(returnArray);
1905  }
1906  default:
1907  {
1908  // this isn't actually possible, just putting this here to get rid
1909  // of the compiler warning.
1910  return std::move(NdArray<double>(0));
1911  }
1912  }

1932  // Method Description:
1949  template<typename dtype>
1950  NdArray<dtype> bincount(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, uint16 inMinLength)
1951  {
1952  // only works with integer input types
1953  static_assert(DtypeInfo<dtype>::isInteger(), "ERROR: bincount: can only use with integer types.");
1954 
1955  dtype maxValue = inArray.max().item();
1956  if (maxValue < 0)
1957  {
1958  // no positive values so just return an empty array
1959  return std::move(NdArray<dtype>(0));
1960  }
1961 
1962  if (maxValue + 1 > DtypeInfo<dtype>::max())
1963  {
1964  std::string errStr = "Error: bincount: array values too large, will result in gigantic array that will take up alot of memory...";
1965  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1966  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1967  }
1968 
1969  uint16 outArraySize = std::max(static_cast<uint16>(maxValue + 1), inMinLength);
1970  NdArray<dtype> clippedArray = inArray.clip(0, maxValue);
1971 
1972  NdArray<dtype> outArray(1, outArraySize);
1973  outArray.zeros();
1974  for (uint32 i = 0; i < inArray.size(); ++i)
1975  {
1976  ++outArray[clippedArray[i]];
1977  }
1978 
1979  return std::move(outArray);
1980  }

2235  // Method Description:
2245  template<typename dtype>
2246  NdArray<dtype> column_stack(const std::initializer_list<NdArray<dtype> >& inArrayList)
2247  {
2248  // first loop through to calculate the final size of the array
2249  typename std::initializer_list<NdArray<dtype> >::iterator iter;
2250  Shape finalShape;
2251  for (iter = inArrayList.begin(); iter < inArrayList.end(); ++iter)
2252  {
2253  if (finalShape.isnull())
2254  {
2255  finalShape = iter->shape();
2256  }
2257  else if (iter->shape().rows != finalShape.rows)
2258  {
2259  std::string errStr = "ERROR: column_stack: input arrays must have the same number of rows.";
2260  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
2261  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
2262  }
2263  else
2264  {
2265  finalShape.cols += iter->shape().cols;
2266  }
2267  }
2268 
2269  // now that we know the final size, contruct the output array
2270  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(finalShape);
2271  uint32 colStart = 0;
2272  for (iter = inArrayList.begin(); iter < inArrayList.end(); ++iter)
2273  {
2274  Shape theShape = iter->shape();
2275  for (uint32 row = 0; row < theShape.rows; ++row)
2276  {
2277  for (uint32 col = 0; col < theShape.cols; ++col)
2278  {
2279  returnArray(row, colStart + col) = iter->operator()(row, col);
2280  }
2281  }
2282  colStart += theShape.cols;
2283  }
2284 
2285  return std::move(returnArray);
2286  }

2564  if (inArray1.shape() != inArray2.shape())
2565  {
2566  std::string errStr = "ERROR: cross: the input array dimensions are not consistant.";
2567  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
2568  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
2569  }
2570 
2571  switch (inAxis)
2572  {
2573  case Axis::NONE:
2574  {
2575  uint32 arraySize = inArray1.size();
2576  if (arraySize != inArray2.size() || arraySize < 2 || arraySize > 3)
2577  {
2578  std::string errStr = "ERROR: cross: incompatible dimensions for cross product (dimension must be 2 or 3)";
2579  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
2580  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
2581  }
2582 
2583  NdArray<dtype> in1 = inArray1.flatten();
2584  NdArray<dtype> in2 = inArray2.flatten();
2585 
2586  switch (arraySize)
2587  {
2588  case 2:
2589  {
2590  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { static_cast<dtypeOut>(in1[0]) * static_cast<dtypeOut>(in2[1])
2591  - static_cast<dtypeOut>(in1[1]) * static_cast<dtypeOut>(in2[0]) };
2592  return std::move(returnArray);
2593  }
2594  case 3:
2595  {
2596  dtypeOut i = static_cast<dtypeOut>(in1[1]) * static_cast<dtypeOut>(in2[2])
2597  - static_cast<dtypeOut>(in1[2]) * static_cast<dtypeOut>(in2[1]);
2598  dtypeOut j = -(static_cast<dtypeOut>(in1[0]) * static_cast<dtypeOut>(in2[2])
2599  - static_cast<dtypeOut>(in1[2]) * static_cast<dtypeOut>(in2[0]));
2600  dtypeOut k = (static_cast<dtypeOut>(in1[0]) * static_cast<dtypeOut>(in2[1])
2601  - static_cast<dtypeOut>(in1[1]) * static_cast<dtypeOut>(in2[0]));
2602 
2603  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { i, j, k };
2604  return std::move(returnArray);
2605  }
2606  default:
2607  {
2608  // this isn't actually possible, just putting this here to get rid
2609  // of the compiler warning.
2610  return std::move(NdArray<dtypeOut>(0));
2611  }
2612  }
2613  }
2614  case Axis::ROW:
2615  {
2616  Shape arrayShape = inArray1.shape();
2617  if (arrayShape != inArray2.shape() || arrayShape.rows < 2 || arrayShape.rows > 3)
2618  {
2619  std::string errStr = "ERROR: cross: incompatible dimensions for cross product (dimension must be 2 or 3)";
2620  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
2621  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
2622  }
2623 
2624  Shape returnArrayShape;
2625  if (arrayShape.rows == 2)
2626  {
2627  returnArrayShape = Shape(1, arrayShape.cols);
2628  }
2629  else
2630  {
2631  returnArrayShape = Shape(3, arrayShape.cols);
2632  }
2633 
2634  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray(returnArrayShape);
2635  for (uint32 col = 0; col < arrayShape.cols; ++col)
2636  {
2637  int32 theCol = static_cast<int32>(col);
2638  NdArray<dtype> vec1 = inArray1({ 0, static_cast<int32>(arrayShape.rows) }, { theCol, theCol + 1 });
2639  NdArray<dtype> vec2 = inArray2({ 0, static_cast<int32>(arrayShape.rows) }, { theCol, theCol + 1 });
2640  NdArray<dtypeOut> vecCross = cross<dtypeOut>(vec1, vec2, Axis::NONE);
2641 
2642  returnArray.put({ 0, static_cast<int32>(returnArrayShape.rows) }, { theCol, theCol + 1 }, vecCross);
2643  }
2644 
2645  return std::move(returnArray);
2646  }
2647  case Axis::COL:
2648  {
2649  Shape arrayShape = inArray1.shape();
2650  if (arrayShape != inArray2.shape() || arrayShape.cols < 2 || arrayShape.cols > 3)
2651  {
2652  std::string errStr = "ERROR: cross: incompatible dimensions for cross product (dimension must be 2 or 3)";
2653  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
2654  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
2655  }
2656 
2657  Shape returnArrayShape;
2658  if (arrayShape.cols == 2)
2659  {
2660  returnArrayShape = Shape(arrayShape.rows, 1);
2661  }
2662  else
2663  {
2664  returnArrayShape = Shape(arrayShape.rows, 3);
2665  }
2666 
2667  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray(returnArrayShape);
2668  for (uint32 row = 0; row < arrayShape.rows; ++row)
2669  {
2670  int32 theRow = static_cast<int32>(row);
2671  NdArray<dtype> vec1 = inArray1({ theRow, theRow + 1 }, { 0, static_cast<int32>(arrayShape.cols) });
2672  NdArray<dtype> vec2 = inArray2({ theRow, theRow + 1 }, { 0, static_cast<int32>(arrayShape.cols) });
2673  NdArray<dtypeOut> vecCross = cross<dtypeOut>(vec1, vec2, Axis::NONE);
2674 
2675  returnArray.put({ theRow, theRow + 1 }, { 0, static_cast<int32>(returnArrayShape.cols) }, vecCross);
2676  }
2677 
2678  return std::move(returnArray);
2679  }
2680  default:
2681  {
2682  // this isn't actually possible, just putting this here to get rid
2683  // of the compiler warning.
2684  return std::move(NdArray<dtypeOut>(0));

2828  // Method Description:
2837  template<typename dtype>
2838  NdArray<dtype> deleteIndices(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, const NdArray<uint32>& inArrayIdxs, Axis inAxis)
2839  {
2840  // make sure that the indices are unique first
2841  NdArray<uint32> indices = unique(inArrayIdxs);
2842 
2843  switch (inAxis)
2844  {
2845  case Axis::NONE:
2846  {
2847  std::vector<dtype> values;
2848  for (uint32 i = 0; i < inArray.size(); ++i)
2849  {
2850  if (indices.contains(i).item())
2851  {
2852  continue;
2853  }
2854 
2855  values.push_back(inArray[i]);
2856  }
2857 
2858  return std::move(NdArray<dtype>(values));
2859  }
2860  case Axis::ROW:
2861  {
2862  Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
2863  if (indices.max().item() >= inShape.rows)
2864  {
2865  std::string errStr = "ERROR: deleteIndices: input index value is greater than the number of rows in the array.";
2866  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
2867  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
2868  }
2869 
2870  uint32 numNewRows = inShape.rows - indices.size();
2871  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(numNewRows, inShape.cols);
2872 
2873  uint32 rowCounter = 0;
2874  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
2875  {
2876  if (indices.contains(row).item())
2877  {
2878  continue;
2879  }
2880 
2881  for (uint32 col = 0; col < inShape.cols; ++col)
2882  {
2883  returnArray(rowCounter, col) = inArray(row, col);
2884  }
2885  ++rowCounter;
2886  }
2887 
2888  return std::move(returnArray);
2889  }
2890  case Axis::COL:
2891  {
2892  Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
2893  if (indices.max().item() >= inShape.cols)
2894  {
2895  std::string errStr = "ERROR: deleteIndices: input index value is greater than the number of cols in the array.";
2896  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
2897  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
2898  }
2899 
2900  uint32 numNewCols = inShape.cols - indices.size();
2901  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(inShape.rows, numNewCols);
2902 
2903  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
2904  {
2905  uint32 colCounter = 0;
2906  for (uint32 col = 0; col < inShape.cols; ++col)
2907  {
2908  if (indices.contains(col).item())
2909  {
2910  continue;
2911  }
2912 
2913  returnArray(row, colCounter++) = inArray(row, col);
2914  }
2915  }
2916 
2917  return std::move(returnArray);
2918 
2919 
2920  }
2921  default:
2922  {
2923  // this isn't actually possible, just putting this here to get rid
2924  // of the compiler warning.
2925  return std::move(NdArray<dtype>(0));
2926  }
2927  }
2928  }

2969

4165  // Method Description:
4176  template<typename dtype>
4177  NdArray<double> gradient(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, Axis inAxis)
4178  {
4179  switch (inAxis)
4180  {
4181  case Axis::ROW:
4182  {
4183  auto inShape = inArray.shape();
4184  if (inShape.rows < 2)
4185  {
4186  std::string errStr = "ERROR: gradient: input array must have more than 1 row.";
4187  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
4188  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
4189  }
4190 
4191  // first do the first and last rows
4192  auto returnArray = NdArray<double>(inShape);
4193  for (uint32 col = 0; col < inShape.cols; ++col)
4194  {
4195  returnArray(0, col) = static_cast<double>(inArray(1, col)) - static_cast<double>(inArray(0, col));
4196  returnArray(-1, col) = static_cast<double>(inArray(-1, col)) - static_cast<double>(inArray(-2, col));
4197  }
4198 
4199  // then rip through the rest of the array
4200  for (uint32 col = 0; col < inShape.cols; ++col)
4201  {
4202  for (uint32 row = 1; row < inShape.rows - 1; ++row)
4203  {
4204  returnArray(row, col) = (static_cast<double>(inArray(row + 1, col)) - static_cast<double>(inArray(row - 1, col))) / 2.0;
4205  }
4206  }
4207 
4208  return std::move(returnArray);
4209  }
4210  case Axis::COL:
4211  {
4212  auto inShape = inArray.shape();
4213  if (inShape.cols < 2)
4214  {
4215  std::string errStr = "ERROR: gradient: input array must have more than 1 columns.";
4216  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
4217  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
4218  }
4219 
4220  // first do the first and last columns
4221  auto returnArray = NdArray<double>(inShape);
4222  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
4223  {
4224  returnArray(row, 0) = static_cast<double>(inArray(row, 1)) - static_cast<double>(inArray(row, 0));
4225  returnArray(row, -1) = static_cast<double>(inArray(row, -1)) - static_cast<double>(inArray(row, -2));
4226  }
4227 
4228  // then rip through the rest of the array
4229  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
4230  {
4231  for (uint32 col = 1; col < inShape.cols - 1; ++col)
4232  {
4233  returnArray(row, col) = (static_cast<double>(inArray(row, col + 1)) - static_cast<double>(inArray(row, col - 1))) / 2.0;
4234  }
4235  }
4236 
4237  return std::move(returnArray);
4238  }
4239  default:
4240  {
4241  // will return the gradient of the flattened array
4242  if (inArray.size() < 2)
4243  {
4244  std::string errStr = "ERROR: gradient: input array must have more than 1 element.";
4245  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
4246  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
4247  }
4248

4251  returnArray[-1] = static_cast<double>(inArray[-1]) - static_cast<double>(inArray[-2]);
4252  for (uint32 i = 1; i < inArray.size() - 1; ++i)
4253  {
4254  returnArray[i] = (static_cast<double>(inArray[i + 1]) - static_cast<double>(inArray[i - 1])) / 2.0;

4299  // Method Description:
4311  template<typename dtype>
4312  std::pair<NdArray<uint32>, NdArray<double> > histogram(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, uint32 inNumBins)
4313  {
4314  if (inNumBins == 0)
4315  {
4316  std::string errStr = "ERROR: histogram: number of bins must be positive.";
4317  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
4318  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
4319  }
4320 
4321  NdArray<uint32> histo = zeros<uint32>(1, inNumBins);
4322 
4323  bool useEndPoint = true;
4324  NdArray<double> binEdges = linspace(static_cast<double>(inArray.min().item()),
4325  static_cast<double>(inArray.max().item()), inNumBins + 1, useEndPoint);
4326 
4327  for (uint32 i = 0; i < inArray.size(); ++i)
4328  {
4329  // binary search to find the bin idx
4330  bool keepSearching = true;
4331  uint32 lowIdx = 0;
4332  uint32 highIdx = binEdges.size() - 1;
4333  while (keepSearching)
4334  {
4335  uint32 idx = (lowIdx + highIdx) / 2; // integer division
4336  if (lowIdx == highIdx || lowIdx == highIdx - 1)
4337  {
4338  // we found the bin
4339  ++histo[lowIdx];
4340  break;
4341  }
4342 
4343  if (inArray[i] > binEdges[idx])
4344  {
4345  lowIdx = idx;
4346  }
4347  else if (inArray[i] < binEdges[idx])
4348  {
4349  highIdx = idx;
4350  }
4351  else
4352  {
4353  // we found the bin
4354  ++histo[idx];
4355  break;
4356  }
4357  }
4358  }
4359 
4360  return std::move(std::make_pair(histo, binEdges));
4361  }

4496  template<typename dtype>
4497  NdArray<dtype> interp(const NdArray<dtype>& inX, const NdArray<dtype>& inXp, const NdArray<dtype>& inFp)
4498  {

4500  if (inXp.size() != inFp.size())
4501  {
4502  std::string errStr = "ERROR: interp: inXp and inFp need to be the same size().";
4503  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
4504  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
4505  }
4506 
4507  if (inX.min().item() < inXp.min().item() || inX.max().item() > inXp.max().item())
4508  {
4509  std::string errStr = "ERROR: interp: endpoints of inX should be contained within inXp.";
4510  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
4511  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
4512  }
4513 
4514  // sort the input inXp and inFp data
4515  NdArray<uint32> sortedXpIdxs = argsort(inXp);
4516  NdArray<dtype> sortedXp(1, inFp.size());
4517  NdArray<dtype> sortedFp(1, inFp.size());
4518  for (uint32 i = 0; i < sortedXpIdxs.size(); ++i)
4519  {
4520  sortedXp[i] = inXp[sortedXpIdxs[i]];
4521  sortedFp[i] = inFp[sortedXpIdxs[i]];
4522  }
4523 
4524  // sort the input inX array
4525  NdArray<dtype> sortedX = sort(inX);
4526 
4527  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, inX.size());
4528 
4529  uint32 currXpIdx = 0;
4530  uint32 currXidx = 0;
4531  while (currXidx < sortedX.size())
4532  {
4533  if (sortedXp[currXpIdx] <= sortedX[currXidx] && sortedX[currXidx] <= sortedXp[currXpIdx + 1])
4534  {
4535  double percent = static_cast<double>(sortedX[currXidx] - sortedXp[currXpIdx]) /
4536  static_cast<double>(sortedXp[currXpIdx + 1] - sortedXp[currXpIdx]);
4537  returnArray[currXidx++] = Utils::interp(sortedFp[currXpIdx], sortedFp[currXpIdx + 1], percent);
4538  }
4539  else

4542  }

4871  {

4873  {
4874  return std::move(NdArray<dtype>(0));
4875  }
4876  else if (inNum == 1)
4877  {
4878  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { inStart };
4879  return std::move(returnArray);
4880  }
4881 
4882  if (inStop <= inStart)
4883  {
4884  std::string errStr = "ERROR: linspace: stop value must be greater than the start value.";
4885  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
4886  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
4887  }
4888 
4889  if (endPoint)
4890  {
4891  if (inNum == 2)
4892  {
4893  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { inStart, inStop };
4894  return std::move(returnArray);
4895  }
4896  else
4897  {
4898  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, inNum);
4899  returnArray[0] = inStart;
4900  returnArray[inNum - 1] = inStop;
4901 
4902  dtype step = (inStop - inStart) / (inNum - 1);
4903  for (uint32 i = 1; i < inNum - 1; ++i)
4904  {
4905  returnArray[i] = returnArray[i - 1] + step;
4906  }
4907 
4908  return std::move(returnArray);
4909  }
4910  }
4911  else
4912  {
4913  if (inNum == 2)
4914  {
4915  dtype step = (inStop - inStart) / (inNum);
4916  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { inStart, inStart + step };
4917  return std::move(returnArray);
4918  }
4919  else
4920  {
4921  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, inNum);
4922  returnArray[0] = inStart;
4923 
4924  dtype step = (inStop - inStart) / inNum;
4925  for (uint32 i = 1; i < inNum; ++i)
4926  {
4927  returnArray[i] = returnArray[i - 1] + step;
4928  }
4929 
4930  return std::move(returnArray);
4931  }
4932  }

5602  //============================================================================
5603  // Method Description:
5614  template<typename dtype>
5615  NdArray<double> nanmean(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, Axis inAxis)
5616  {
5617  switch (inAxis)
5618  {
5619  case Axis::NONE:
5620  {
5621  double sum = static_cast<double>(std::accumulate(inArray.cbegin(), inArray.cend(), 0.0,
5622  [](dtype inValue1, dtype inValue2) { return std::isnan(inValue2) ? inValue1 : inValue1 + inValue2; }));
5623 
5624  double numberNonNan = static_cast<double>(std::accumulate(inArray.cbegin(), inArray.cend(), 0.0,
5625  [](dtype inValue1, dtype inValue2) { return std::isnan(inValue2) ? inValue1 : inValue1 + 1; }));
5626 
5627  NdArray<double> returnArray = { sum /= numberNonNan };
5628 
5629  return std::move(returnArray);
5630  }
5631  case Axis::COL:
5632  {
5633  Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
5634  NdArray<double> returnArray(1, inShape.rows);
5635  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
5636  {
5637  double sum = static_cast<double>(std::accumulate(inArray.cbegin(row), inArray.cend(row), 0.0,
5638  [](dtype inValue1, dtype inValue2) { return std::isnan(inValue2) ? inValue1 : inValue1 + inValue2; }));
5639 
5640  double numberNonNan = static_cast<double>(std::accumulate(inArray.cbegin(row), inArray.cend(row), 0.0,

5791  // Method Description:
5803  template<typename dtypeOut = double, typename dtype>
5804  NdArray<double> nanpercentile(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, double inPercentile, Axis inAxis, const std::string& inInterpMethod)
5805  {
5806  if (inPercentile < 0.0 || inPercentile > 100.0)
5807  {
5808  std::string errStr = "ERROR: percentile: input percentile value must be of the range [0, 100].";
5809  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
5810  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
5811  }
5812 
5813  if (inInterpMethod.compare("linear") != 0 &&
5814  inInterpMethod.compare("lower") != 0 &&
5815  inInterpMethod.compare("higher") != 0 &&
5816  inInterpMethod.compare("nearest") != 0 &&
5817  inInterpMethod.compare("midpoint") != 0)
5818  {
5819  std::string errStr = "ERROR: percentile: input interpolation method is not a vaid option.\n";
5820  errStr += "\tValid options are 'linear', 'lower', 'higher', 'nearest', 'midpoint'.";
5821  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
5822  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
5823  }
5824 
5825  switch (inAxis)
5826  {
5827  case Axis::NONE:
5828  {
5829  if (Utils::essentiallyEqual(inPercentile, 0.0))
5830  {
5831  for (uint32 i = 0; i < inArray.size(); ++i)
5832  {
5833  if (!isnan(inArray[i]))
5834  {
5835  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { static_cast<dtypeOut>(inArray[i]) };
5836  return std::move(returnArray);
5837  }
5838  }
5839  return std::move(NdArray<dtypeOut>(0));
5840  }
5841  else if (Utils::essentiallyEqual(inPercentile, 100.0))
5842  {
5843  for (int32 i = static_cast<int32>(inArray.size()) - 1; i > -1; --i)
5844  {
5845  if (!isnan(inArray[i]))
5846  {
5847  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { static_cast<dtypeOut>(inArray[i]) };
5848  return std::move(returnArray);
5849  }
5850  }
5851  return std::move(NdArray<dtypeOut>(0));
5852  }
5853 
5854  std::vector<double> arrayCopy;
5855  uint32 numNonNan = 0;
5856  for (uint32 j = 0; j < inArray.size(); ++j)
5857  {
5858  if (!isnan(inArray[j]))
5859  {
5860  arrayCopy.push_back(inArray[j]);
5861  ++numNonNan;
5862  }
5863  }
5864 
5865  if (arrayCopy.size() < 2)
5866  {
5867  return std::move(NdArray<dtypeOut>(0));
5868  }
5869 
5870  int32 i = static_cast<int32>(std::floor(static_cast<double>(numNonNan - 1) * inPercentile / 100.0));
5871  uint32 indexLower = static_cast<uint32>(clip<uint32>(i, 0, numNonNan - 2));
5872 
5873  std::sort(arrayCopy.begin(), arrayCopy.end());
5874 
5875  if (inInterpMethod.compare("linear") == 0)
5876  {
5877  double percentI = static_cast<double>(indexLower) / static_cast<double>(numNonNan - 1);
5878  double fraction = (inPercentile / 100.0 - percentI) /
5879  (static_cast<double>(indexLower + 1) / static_cast<double>(numNonNan - 1) - percentI);
5880 
5881  double returnValue = arrayCopy[indexLower] + (arrayCopy[indexLower + 1] - arrayCopy[indexLower]) * fraction;
5882  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { static_cast<dtypeOut>(returnValue) };
5883  return std::move(returnArray);
5884  }
5885  else if (inInterpMethod.compare("lower") == 0)
5886  {
5887  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { static_cast<dtypeOut>(arrayCopy[indexLower]) };
5888  return std::move(returnArray);
5889  }
5890  else if (inInterpMethod.compare("higher") == 0)
5891  {
5892  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { static_cast<dtypeOut>(arrayCopy[indexLower + 1]) };
5893  return std::move(returnArray);
5894  }
5895  else if (inInterpMethod.compare("nearest") == 0)
5896  {
5897  double percent = inPercentile / 100.0;
5898  double percent1 = static_cast<double>(indexLower) / static_cast<double>(numNonNan - 1);
5899  double percent2 = static_cast<double>(indexLower + 1) / static_cast<double>(numNonNan - 1);
5900  double diff1 = percent - percent1;
5901  double diff2 = percent2 - percent;
5902 
5903  switch (argmin<double>({ diff1, diff2 }).item())
5904  {
5905  case 0:
5906  {
5907  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { static_cast<dtypeOut>(arrayCopy[indexLower]) };
5908  return std::move(returnArray);
5909  }
5910  case 1:
5911  {
5912  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { static_cast<dtypeOut>(arrayCopy[indexLower + 1]) };
5913  return std::move(returnArray);
5914  }
5915  }
5916  }
5917  else if (inInterpMethod.compare("midpoint") == 0)
5918  {
5919  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { (arrayCopy[indexLower] + arrayCopy[indexLower + 1]) / 2.0 };
5920  return std::move(returnArray);
5921  }
5922  }
5923  case Axis::COL:
5924  {
5925  Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
5926 
5927  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray(1, inShape.rows);
5928  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
5929  {
5930  NdArray<dtypeOut> outValue = nanpercentile<dtypeOut>(NdArray<dtype>(inArray.cbegin(row), inArray.cend(row)),
5931  inPercentile, Axis::NONE, inInterpMethod);
5932 
5933  if (outValue.size() == 1)
5934  {
5935  returnArray[row] = outValue.item();
5936  }
5937  else
5938  {
5939  returnArray[row] = Constants::nan;
5940  }
5941  }
5942 
5943  return std::move(returnArray);
5944  }
5945  case Axis::ROW:
5946  {
5947  NdArray<dtype> arrayTrans = inArray.transpose();
5948  Shape inShape = arrayTrans.shape();
5949 
5950  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray(1, inShape.rows);
5951  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
5952  {
5953  NdArray<dtypeOut> outValue = nanpercentile<dtypeOut>(NdArray<dtype>(arrayTrans.cbegin(row), arrayTrans.cend(row)),
5954  inPercentile, Axis::NONE, inInterpMethod);
5955 
5956  if (outValue.size() == 1)
5957  {
5958  returnArray[row] = outValue.item();
5959  }
5960  else
5961  {
5962  returnArray[row] = Constants::nan;
5963  }
5964  }
5965 
5966  return std::move(returnArray);
5967  }
5968  default:
5969  {
5970  // this isn't actually possible, just putting this here to get rid
5971  // of the compiler warning.
5972  return std::move(NdArray<dtypeOut>(0));
5973  }
5974  }
5975  }

6521  std::sort(arrayCopy.begin(), arrayCopy.end());
6522 
6523  if (inInterpMethod.compare("linear") == 0)
6524  {
6525  double percentI = static_cast<double>(indexLower) / static_cast<double>(inArray.size() - 1);
6526  double fraction = (inPercentile / 100.0 - percentI) /
6527  (static_cast<double>(indexLower + 1) / static_cast<double>(inArray.size() - 1) - percentI);
6528 
6529  double returnValue = arrayCopy[indexLower] + (arrayCopy[indexLower + 1] - arrayCopy[indexLower]) * fraction;
6530  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { static_cast<dtypeOut>(returnValue) };
6531  return std::move(returnArray);
6532  }
6533  else if (inInterpMethod.compare("lower") == 0)
6534  {
6535  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { static_cast<dtypeOut>(arrayCopy[indexLower]) };
6536  return std::move(returnArray);
6537  }
6538  else if (inInterpMethod.compare("higher") == 0)
6539  {
6540  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { static_cast<dtypeOut>(arrayCopy[indexLower + 1]) };
6541  return std::move(returnArray);
6542  }
6543  else if (inInterpMethod.compare("nearest") == 0)
6544  {
6545  double percent = inPercentile / 100.0;
6546  double percent1 = static_cast<double>(indexLower) / static_cast<double>(inArray.size() - 1);
6547  double percent2 = static_cast<double>(indexLower + 1) / static_cast<double>(inArray.size() - 1);
6548  double diff1 = percent - percent1;
6549  double diff2 = percent2 - percent;
6550 
6551  switch (argmin<double>({ diff1, diff2 }).item())
6552  {
6553  case 0:
6554  {
6555  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { static_cast<dtypeOut>(arrayCopy[indexLower]) };
6556  return std::move(returnArray);
6557  }
6558  case 1:
6559  {
6560  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { static_cast<dtypeOut>(arrayCopy[indexLower + 1]) };
6561  return std::move(returnArray);
6562  }
6563  }
6564  }
6565  else if (inInterpMethod.compare("midpoint") == 0)
6566  {
6567  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { static_cast<dtypeOut>((arrayCopy[indexLower] + arrayCopy[indexLower + 1]) / 2.0) };
6568  return std::move(returnArray);
6569  }
6570  }
6571  case Axis::COL:
6572  {
6573  Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
6574 
6575  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray(1, inShape.rows);
6576  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
6577  {
6578  returnArray[row] = percentile<dtypeOut>(NdArray<dtype>(inArray.cbegin(row), inArray.cend(row)),
6579  inPercentile, Axis::NONE, inInterpMethod).item();
6580  }
6581 
6582  return std::move(returnArray);
6583  }
6584  case Axis::ROW:
6585  {
6586  NdArray<dtype> arrayTrans = inArray.transpose();
6587  Shape inShape = arrayTrans.shape();
6588 
6589  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray(1, inShape.rows);
6590  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
6591  {
6592  returnArray[row] = percentile<dtypeOut>(NdArray<dtype>(arrayTrans.cbegin(row), arrayTrans.cend(row)),
6593  inPercentile, Axis::NONE, inInterpMethod).item();
6594  }
6595 
6596  return std::move(returnArray);
6597  }
6598  default:
6599  {
6600  // this isn't actually possible, just putting this here to get rid
6601  // of the compiler warning.
6602  return std::move(NdArray<dtypeOut>(0));
6603  }
6604  }
6605  }

7166  template<typename dtype>
7167  NdArray<dtype> roll(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, int32 inShift, Axis inAxis)
7168  {
7169  switch (inAxis)
7170  {
7171  case Axis::NONE:
7172  {
7173  uint32 shift = std::abs(inShift) % inArray.size();
7174  if (inShift > 0)
7175  {
7176  shift = inArray.size() - shift;
7177  }
7178 
7179  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(inArray);
7180  std::rotate(returnArray.begin(), returnArray.begin() + shift, returnArray.end());
7181 
7182  return std::move(returnArray);
7183  }
7184  case Axis::COL:
7185  {
7186  Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
7187 
7188  uint32 shift = std::abs(inShift) % inShape.cols;
7189  if (inShift > 0)
7190  {
7191  shift = inShape.cols - shift;
7192  }
7193 
7194  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(inArray);
7195  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
7196  {
7197  std::rotate(returnArray.begin(row), returnArray.begin(row) + shift, returnArray.end(row));
7198  }
7199 
7200  return std::move(returnArray);
7201  }
7202  case Axis::ROW:
7203  {
7204  Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
7205 
7206  uint32 shift = std::abs(inShift) % inShape.rows;
7207  if (inShift > 0)
7208  {
7209  shift = inShape.rows - shift;
7210  }
7211 
7212  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = inArray.transpose();
7213  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.cols; ++row)
7214  {
7215  std::rotate(returnArray.begin(row), returnArray.begin(row) + shift, returnArray.end(row));
7216  }
7217 
7218  return std::move(returnArray.transpose());
7219  }
7220  default:
7221  {
7222  // this isn't actually possible, just putting this here to get rid
7223  // of the compiler warning.
7224  return std::move(NdArray<dtype>(0));
7225  }
7226  }

7302  // Method Description:
7311  template<typename dtype>
7312  NdArray<dtype> row_stack(const std::initializer_list<NdArray<dtype> >& inArrayList)
7313  {
7314  // first loop through to calculate the final size of the array
7315  typename std::initializer_list<NdArray<dtype> >::iterator iter;
7316  Shape finalShape;
7317  for (iter = inArrayList.begin(); iter < inArrayList.end(); ++iter)
7318  {
7319  if (finalShape.isnull())
7320  {
7321  finalShape = iter->shape();
7322  }
7323  else if (iter->shape().cols != finalShape.cols)
7324  {
7325  std::string errStr = "ERROR: row_stack: input arrays must have the same number of columns.";
7326  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
7327  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
7328  }
7329  else
7330  {
7331  finalShape.rows += iter->shape().rows;
7332  }
7333  }
7334 
7335  // now that we know the final size, contruct the output array
7336  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(finalShape);
7337  uint32 rowStart = 0;
7338  for (iter = inArrayList.begin(); iter < inArrayList.end(); ++iter)
7339  {
7340  Shape theShape = iter->shape();
7341  for (uint32 row = 0; row < theShape.rows; ++row)
7342  {
7343  for (uint32 col = 0; col < theShape.cols; ++col)
7344  {
7345  returnArray(rowStart + row, col) = iter->operator()(row, col);
7346  }
7347  }
7348  rowStart += theShape.rows;
7349  }
7350 
7351  return std::move(returnArray);
7352  }

8343  // Method Description:
8354  template<typename dtype>
8355  NdArray<dtype> trim_zeros(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, const std::string inTrim)
8356  {
8357  if (inTrim == "f")
8358  {
8359  uint32 place = 0;
8360  for (uint32 i = 0; i < inArray.size(); ++i)
8361  {
8362  if (inArray[i] != static_cast<dtype>(0))
8363  {
8364  break;
8365  }
8366  else
8367  {
8368  ++place;
8369  }
8370  }
8371 
8372  if (place == inArray.size())
8373  {
8374  return std::move(NdArray<dtype>(0));
8375  }
8376 
8377  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, inArray.size() - place);
8378  std::copy(inArray.cbegin() + place, inArray.cend(), returnArray.begin());
8379 
8380  return std::move(returnArray);
8381  }
8382  else if (inTrim == "b")
8383  {
8384  uint32 place = inArray.size();
8385  for (uint32 i = inArray.size() - 1; i > 0; --i)
8386  {
8387  if (inArray[i] != static_cast<dtype>(0))
8388  {
8389  break;
8390  }
8391  else
8392  {
8393  --place;
8394  }
8395  }
8396 
8397  if (place == 0 || (place == 1 && inArray[0] == 0))
8398  {
8399  return std::move(NdArray<dtype>(0));
8400  }
8401 
8402  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, place);
8403  std::copy(inArray.cbegin(), inArray.cbegin() + place, returnArray.begin());
8404 
8405  return std::move(returnArray);
8406  }
8407  else if (inTrim == "fb")
8408  {
8409  uint32 placeBegin = 0;
8410  for (uint32 i = 0; i < inArray.size(); ++i)
8411  {
8412  if (inArray[i] != static_cast<dtype>(0))
8413  {
8414  break;
8415  }
8416  else
8417  {
8418  ++placeBegin;
8419  }
8420  }
8421 
8422  if (placeBegin == inArray.size())
8423  {
8424  return std::move(NdArray<dtype>(0));
8425  }
8426 
8427  uint32 placeEnd = inArray.size();
8428  for (uint32 i = inArray.size() - 1; i > 0; --i)
8429  {
8430  if (inArray[i] != static_cast<dtype>(0))
8431  {
8432  break;
8433  }
8434  else
8435  {
8436  --placeEnd;
8437  }
8438  }
8439 
8440  if (placeEnd == 0 || (placeEnd == 1 && inArray[0] == 0))
8441  {
8442  return std::move(NdArray<dtype>(0));
8443  }
8444 
8445  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, placeEnd - placeBegin);
8446  std::copy(inArray.cbegin() + placeBegin, inArray.cbegin() + placeEnd, returnArray.begin());
8447 
8448  return std::move(returnArray);
8449  }
8450  else
8451  {
8452  std::string errStr = "ERROR: trim_zeros: trim options are 'f' = front, 'b' = back, 'fb' = front and back.";
8453  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
8454  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
8455  }
8456  }
